06/05/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH Minister of Security Barisa Colak and Turkish Interior Minister Abdulkadir Aksu signed a statement Thursday (5 May) on concrete measures against terrorism. 
All of them are in line with the 2000 agreement between the BiH Council of Ministers and the Turkish government regarding the fight against terrorism, organised crime and drug smuggling. 
Colak noted the importance of exchanging information in tackling these issues, while Aksu offered Turkish help in training local authorities. 
Turkey is also ready to provide help in reforming the BiH police. 
(Fena, BiH CoM, PBS BiH - 05/05/05)
